1
00:48:24,660 --> 00:48:26,828
KILI:
Come on! Get up!

2
00:48:27,121 --> 00:48:28,412
-Bilbo!
-Don't!

3
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:32,041
Lay down your arms...

4
00:48:32,709 --> 00:48:34,502
...or we'll rip his off.

5
00:48:42,219 --> 00:48:43,678
[SWORD CLANGS]

6
00:48:49,143 --> 00:48:51,144
NORI:
Oh! That's hot, that's hot, that's hot!

7
00:48:51,311 --> 00:48:52,937
Don't bother cooking them.

8
00:48:53,105 --> 00:48:57,358
Let's just sit on them
and squash them into jelly.

9
00:48:57,526 --> 00:49:01,737
They should be sautéed and grilled
with a sprinkle of sage.

10
00:49:01,905 --> 00:49:03,447
BALIN:
Is this really necessary?

11
00:49:03,615 --> 00:49:05,408
That does sound quite nice.

12
00:49:05,576 --> 00:49:07,994
BOMBUR: Untie me, mister.
GLOIN: Eat someone your own size.

13
00:49:08,704 --> 00:49:10,621
WILLIAM:
Never mind the seasoning.

14
00:49:10,789 --> 00:49:12,582
We ain't got all night.

15
00:49:12,749 --> 00:49:16,085
Dawn ain't far away.
Let's get a move on.

16
00:49:16,253 --> 00:49:18,671
I don't fancy being turned to stone.

17
00:49:21,383 --> 00:49:22,717
BILBO:
Wait!

18
00:49:22,885 --> 00:49:25,928
You are making a terrible mistake.

19
00:49:26,096 --> 00:49:28,306
You can't reason with them. They're half-wits!

20
00:49:28,473 --> 00:49:30,558
Half-wits? What does that make us?

21
00:49:31,185 --> 00:49:33,978
I meant with the seasoning.

22
00:49:34,313 --> 00:49:36,939
What about the seasoning?

23
00:49:37,107 --> 00:49:38,357
Well, have you smelt them?

24
00:49:38,692 --> 00:49:42,236
You're gonna need something stronger
than sage before you plate this lot up.

25
00:49:42,404 --> 00:49:45,531
BOMBUR: Traitor!
-What do you know about cooking Dwarf?

26
00:49:46,074 --> 00:49:47,116
BERT:
Shut up.

27
00:49:47,451 --> 00:49:51,120
Let the flurgaburburahobbit talk.

28
00:49:52,039 --> 00:49:54,957
The secret to cooking Dwarf is....

29
00:49:55,125 --> 00:49:58,252
BERT: Yes? Come on. Tell us the secret.
-It's, uh....

30
00:49:58,420 --> 00:50:00,463
Yes, I'm telling you. The secret is...

31
00:50:03,008 --> 00:50:04,759
...to skin them first.

32
00:50:04,927 --> 00:50:06,844
NORI:
What? Skin us?

33
00:50:07,012 --> 00:50:09,555
Tom, get me filleting knife.

34
00:50:09,723 --> 00:50:11,390
I'll skin you, you little--!

35
00:50:11,558 --> 00:50:13,434
DWALIN:
I won't forget that. I won't forget it.

36
00:50:13,602 --> 00:50:15,937
What a load of rubbish.

37
00:50:16,104 --> 00:50:19,023
I've eaten plenty with their skins on.

38
00:50:19,191 --> 00:50:21,567
Scarf them, I say, boots and all.

39
00:50:22,194 --> 00:50:24,487
TOM:
He's right.

40
00:50:24,655 --> 00:50:27,281
Nothing wrong with a bit of raw Dwarf.

41
00:50:29,993 --> 00:50:32,203
Nice and crunchy.

42
00:50:32,537 --> 00:50:35,081
Oh, not that one. He's infected.

43
00:50:35,374 --> 00:50:36,999
-Huh?
-You what?

44
00:50:37,167 --> 00:50:41,295
Yeah, he's got worms in his... tubes.

45
00:50:41,463 --> 00:50:43,422
TOM: Eww!
BOMBUR: Aah!

46
00:50:43,674 --> 00:50:46,968
In fact, they all have.
They're infested with parasites.

47
00:50:47,135 --> 00:50:50,096
It's a terrible business.
I wouldn't risk it. I really wouldn't.

48
00:50:50,264 --> 00:50:52,139
Parasites? Did he say "parasites"?

49
00:50:52,307 --> 00:50:55,101
We don't have parasites. You have parasites!

50
00:50:55,852 --> 00:50:57,770
OIN:
What are you talking about, laddie?

51
00:50:57,938 --> 00:50:59,188
[KILI GRUNTS]

52
00:51:01,316 --> 00:51:03,192
I've got parasites as big as my arm.

53
00:51:03,360 --> 00:51:05,945
Mine are the biggest parasites.
I've got huge parasites.

54
00:51:06,113 --> 00:51:07,780
[DWARVES CHATTERING]

55
00:51:07,990 --> 00:51:09,448
KILI: We're riddled.
ORI: Yes, I'm riddled.

56
00:51:09,616 --> 00:51:10,908
Yes, we are, badly.

57
00:51:11,076 --> 00:51:13,953
What would you have us do, then?

58
00:51:14,121 --> 00:51:15,663
Let them all go?

59
00:51:16,039 --> 00:51:19,375
-Well....
-You think I don't know what you're up to?

60
00:51:19,793 --> 00:51:23,879
This little ferret is taking us for fools.

61
00:51:24,339 --> 00:51:25,881
-Ferret?
-Fools?

62
00:51:26,049 --> 00:51:29,010
GANDALF:
The dawn will take you all!

63
00:51:30,429 --> 00:51:32,054
-Who's that?
-No idea.

64
00:51:32,222 --> 00:51:33,347
Can we eat him too?

65
00:51:36,727 --> 00:51:38,436
[TROLLS GROANING]

66
00:51:52,242 --> 00:51:53,993
[ALL LAUGHING]

67
00:51:59,499 --> 00:52:02,043
Get your foot out of my back.

68
00:52:02,377 --> 00:52:04,628
[GRUNTING]

69
00:52:04,796 --> 00:52:06,797
[DWARVES CHATTERING]

70
00:52:07,861 --> 00:52:09,300
[IMITATES TROLL GROAN]

71
00:52:11,553 --> 00:52:13,721
Where did you go to, if I may ask?

72
00:52:13,889 --> 00:52:15,556
To look ahead.

73
00:52:15,932 --> 00:52:18,768
-What brought you back?
-Looking behind.

74
00:52:19,770 --> 00:52:20,978
Nasty business.

75
00:52:21,146 --> 00:52:22,646
Still, they're all in one piece.

76
00:52:22,814 --> 00:52:24,315
No thanks to your burglar.

77
00:52:25,776 --> 00:52:27,860
He had the nous to play for time.

78
00:52:29,279 --> 00:52:31,655
None of the rest of you thought of that.

